gomodel:SYNGO_214  a      owl:Ontology ;
        rdfs:comment      "Automated change 2026-01-08: GO:0098872 replaced by GO:0099528" , "Rationale: The data in this paper describe how activation of group I mGluRs (mGluR1 and 5) with DHPG mediates an increase in Ca2+ (measured with Fluo-3) accompanied with an inward current (measure with whole-cell pact clamp) in hippocampal CA1 neurons. These effects were blocked by adding a specific mGluR1 antagonist, but not with a specific mGluR5 antagonist.. Experimental description: from M&M:\n\"Electrophysiological recording from rat hippocampal slices. Preparation\nof hippocampal slices was performed as described previously (Marino et al., 1998). Young rats [Sprague Dawley, age postnatal day (P) P15-P20] were anesthetized deeply with isoflurane and decapitated. \"" ;
        lego:modelstate   "production" ;
        dc:contributor    "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-6153-3586" , "https://orcid.org/0000-0002-2666-0758" ;
        dc:date           "2026-01-08" ;
